The ANC Youth League has unveiled its preferred candidates for the party&#8217;s top six positions ahead of its elective conference, with Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma leading the charge as its preferred candidate for President.ANCYL national spokesperson Mlondi Mkhize said the decision was taken at the league s national executive committee (NEC) meeting at the weekend on whom it would endorse to lead the governing party after its December elective conference.Today at Luthuli House the ANCYL also announced its backing of Mpumalanga premier David Mabuza for the position of Deputy President currently occupied by Cyril RamaphosaFree State premier Ace Magashule is tipped for the Secretary General position by the Youth League.The Youth League has also made a call that the ANC have two deputy secretary generals instead of one. According to their Secretary General Njabulo Nzuza the purpose of this would be for monitoring and evaluation to improve overall management.The League have in this regard current deputy SG Jessie Duarte to retain her position and that she should be joined by Police minister Fikile Mbalula.Youth League president Collen Maine said that anyone within the party could be nominated for President however for them it is Dlamini-Zuma who needs to be president now.&#8221; There&#8217;s nothing special about deputy president Cyril Ramaphosa or another member of the ANC,&#8221; said Maine.The ANC s MK Veterans Association (MKMVA) has also endorsed Dlamini-Zuma as ANC president with David Mabuza was listed as her deputy.The ANC Women s League (ANCWL) has also given its nod of approval of DlaminiZuma leading the ANC.Alliance partner The Congress of South African Trade Unions (Cosatu) has endorsed Cyril Ramaphosa to take over as President.Meanwhile the Youth League has called for the scraping of five years experience as a job requirement for certain low level posts.-TNA Reporter